# Quality Gate Criteria

> All criteria must pass before integration approval.

## Gate 1: Spec Compliance

- [ ] All checklist items in `06-spec-checklist.md` are marked `[x]`
- [ ] Every `[x]` item has corresponding code that matches the spec
- [ ] No spec items were skipped or partially implemented

## Gate 2: Code Quality

- [ ] No linting errors in modified files
- [ ] No TypeScript/type errors (if applicable)
- [ ] No unused imports or dead code introduced
- [ ] Naming conventions follow project standards

## Gate 3: Test Coverage

- [ ] All public interfaces have unit tests
- [ ] API endpoints have integration tests (if applicable)
- [ ] All tests pass (`npm test` / project test command)
- [ ] No test files contain `.skip` or `.only`

## Gate 4: Documentation

- [ ] API documentation is up to date
- [ ] CHANGELOG entry added for this change
- [ ] README updated if user-facing behavior changed

## Gate 5: Integration

- [ ] No merge conflicts with main branch
- [ ] CI pipeline passes (if configured)
- [ ] PR description includes spec traceability

